		<ab><cb n="a"/><lb n="1"/> <orig n="unresolved">ται</orig> <w lemma="αὐτός">α<unclear reason="damage">ὐ</unclear>τὴ</w> <w lemma="ἤ">ἢ</w> <orig n="unresolved">τ<unclear reason="damage">ο</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/><orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">ιιαι</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" unit="character" extent="unknown"/><orig n="unresolved">νη</orig> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> 
        <cb n="b"/><lb n="1"/><w lemma="ὁ">ἡ</w> <w lemma="σορός">σορός</w> <w lemma="εἰμί">ἐστιν</w> <w lemma="καί">καὶ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">ὁ</w> <w lemma="ὑπόκειμαι">ὑποκείμεν<supplied reason="lost">ο</supplied><unclear reason="damage">ς</unclear></w> <w lemma="τόπος">τόπος</w><lb n="2"/><persName key="dionysia1" type="attested"><name nymRef="#Αὐρηλία"><expan><abbr>Αὐ<unclear reason="damage">ρ</unclear></abbr><ex>ηλίας</ex></expan></name> <name nymRef="#Διονυσία">Διονυ<unclear reason="damage">σ</unclear>ία<unclear reason="damage">ς</unclear></name></persName> <persName key="stephanus3" type="attested"><name nymRef="#Στέφανος">Στ<unclear reason="damage">εφ</unclear>άνου</name></persName>, <w lemma="ἐν">ἐν</w> <w lemma="ὅς">ᾗ</w> <w lemma="εἰ">ε<supplied reason="lost">ἴ</supplied></w> <w lemma="τις">τις</w> <w lemma="ἕτερος">ἕτερ<lb n="3" break="no"/>ο<unclear reason="damage">ς</unclear></w> <w lemma="βούλομαι">βουληθείη</w> <w lemma="ἐνθάπτω">ἐνθάψαι</w> <w lemma="δίδωμι">δώσει</w> <w lemma="πρόστιμον">πρ<supplied reason="lost">ο</supplied><unclear reason="damage">στ</unclear>έμου</w> <orig n="unresolved"><unclear reason="damage">ο</unclear>ν</orig><lb n="4"/><orig n="unresolved">ο<unclear reason="damage">λτ</unclear>αυ<unclear reason="damage">ι</unclear></orig> <w lemma="ὁ">τῷ</w> <w lemma="ἱερόν">ἱερῷ</w> <w lemma="ὁ">τῆς</w> <space dim="horizontal"/><lb n="5"/><persName key="Aphrodite" type="divine"><name nymRef="#Ἀφροδίτη">Ἀφροδείτης</name></persName> <w lemma="χρυσός">χρύσου</w> <w lemma="οὐνκία">οὐνκίας</w> <w lemma="δύο">δύο</w>.</ab> 
      </div>
         <div type="apparatus">
            <p>The left end fragment of the block was found in 1989,
adding about one letter at the beginning of each line to the text
published in <bibl type="hbi" n="ALA">
                  <title level="m">ALA</title>
               </bibl>.</p>
            <p>ii, l.1. The final <term>sigma</term> of <foreign xml:lang="grc">ὑποκείμεν<supplied reason="lost">ο</supplied>ν</foreign> is written as
<term>epsilon</term>.</p>
            <p>The end of l.3 and the beginning of l.4 are very
uncertain.</p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>b. The coffin and the place
beneath it are <supplied reason="subaudible">the property</supplied> of Aurelia Dionysia, daughter of
Stephanos, in which <supplied reason="explanation">coffin</supplied> if anyone else should wish to bury
<supplied reason="subaudible">anyone</supplied> he will give (?)  of a penalty to the shrine  of Aphrodite two
ounces of gold.</ab>
         </div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>See discussion at <ref type="eAla-text" n="IX.7" target=".xml"/>; for the penalty, and its implications for the date, see <ref type="eAla-text" n="IX.5" target=".xml"/>.</p>
         </div>
